IoT Components Required for Continuous Health Monitoring System


1. ESP8266 / ESP32 – Wi-Fi module for IoT connectivity
GSM Module (SIM800L/SIM900A) – Sends emergency alerts via SMS
2. Sensors for Health Monitoring
Accelerometer (ADXL345/MPU6050) – Detects fetal movements (kicks)
Heartbeat Sensor (MAX30100/MAX30102) – Measures maternal heart rate
Blood Pressure Sensor (BMP180/MPX5050GP) – Monitors maternal blood pressure
Temperature Sensor (DS18B20/DHT11) – Tracks maternal body temperature
3. Display & Power Components
OLED Display / LCD 16x2 – Displays real-time health parameters locally
Rechargeable Battery / Power Adapter – Provides continuous power for portability
4. IoT Cloud & Mobile Connectivity
ThingSpeak / Firebase / Blynk – Cloud platforms for real-time data logging and analysis
Mobile App / Web Dashboard – Displays live data and alerts caregivers remotely
